<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7401> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7401" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor pro consule in Cyrene (Robinson, BMC Cat., Cyrenaica ccxxii-iii, who favors a date after Actium and before 27). G. Perl admits the possibility that Pupius was a quaestor before the triumviral period who gained full imperium in the absence, or upon the departure, of a praetorian governor, but prefers the later date (Klio 52, 1970, 349-351).\n" .
